rockchip: rk3506: make the download/recovery key enter U-Boot RockUSB

Two fixes to the generic download-key path so the Luckfox Lyra Ultra
recovery key (SARADC ch1 "Boot_Key", ~9 raw when pressed) is usable for
flashing:

1. Device-name match. rockchip_dnl_key_pressed() looks for the SARADC with
   strncmp(dev->name, "saradc", 6), but RK3506's DT node is "adc@ff4e8000"
   (node-name "adc"), so the match never succeeded and the key was never
   sampled ("no saradc device found"). Confirmed on hardware: `adc single
   saradc 1` -> -ENODEV while `adc single adc@ff4e8000 1` works. Match any
   UCLASS_ADC device whose name contains "adc" (there is a single SARADC).

2. Enter RockUSB instead of bare BootROM maskrom. The default path only sets
   BOOT_BROM_DOWNLOAD and resets into maskrom; a raw image then needs a
   loader downloaded first (`upgrade_tool db ...`) before `wl 0` works.
   The Lyra defconfig already enables CMD_ROCKUSB and the gadget, and DRAM +
   eMMC are up by board_late_init, so start the U-Boot RockUSB gadget on
   mmc0 directly (so `upgrade_tool wl 0 <img>` works without a separate
   loader download). If rockusb ever returns, fall back to maskrom as before.

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c b/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c
--- a/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-rockchip/boot_mode.c
@@ -5,6 +5,7 @@

 #include <adc.h>
 #include <command.h>
+#include <cli.h>
 #include <env.h>
 #include <log.h>
 #include <asm/io.h>
@@ -51,7 +52,7 @@ __weak int rockchip_dnl_key_pressed(void)

 	ret = -ENODEV;
 	uclass_foreach_dev(dev, uc) {
-		if (!strncmp(dev->name, "saradc", 6)) {
+		if (strstr(dev->name, "adc")) {
 			ret = adc_channel_single_shot(dev->name, 1, &val);
 			break;
 		}
@@ -78,6 +79,11 @@ void rockchip_dnl_mode_check(void)
 {
 	if (rockchip_dnl_key_pressed()) {
 		printf("download key pressed, entering download mode...");
+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_ROCKCHIP_RK3506) && IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_CMD_ROCKUSB)
+		printf("\nentering rockusb mode on mmc0...\n");
+		cli_simple_run_command("rockusb 0 mmc 0", 0);
+		printf("rockusb exited, falling back to bootrom download mode...");
+#endif
 		set_back_to_bootrom_dnl_flag();
 		do_reset(NULL, 0, 0, NULL);
 	}
